column30: Hi folks. Just wanted to share an observation from a friend who works in group and event management at M&T and has been responsible for a large part of daily operations of the vaccine distribution at that site. In the first days the M&T mass vax site opened she observed that there were people coming from all over the state for vaccines and thought ‚Äúthis is great!‚Äù That people are happy to come into Baltimore and vaccines are getting in arms. More recently she said her bosses have pointed out the gross inequity. That although M&T bank is literally in the heart of the city, a grossly disproportionate amount of Baltimore city residents are actually able to get shots. She actually started to pay attention and observed that although today was their first 1000 vaccination day, no one from Baltimore city came to get shots until well into the afternoon. Everyone who was able to get appointment last were from more affluent surrounding counties. To put it quite simply, many Baltimoreans don‚Äôt have the means to snag these appointments. Furthermore, many relay on public trasportation, and the stadium is IDEAL for that, but helping this people connect to actually GET an appointment has been near impossible. To complicate matters more, the Governor and the Mayor have recently had it out via the media, with the Mayor claiming Baltimore hasn‚Äôt received nearly enough supply given our population, as compared to other counties; however the Governor has cited the mass vax site as a supply for Baltimore...problem is, those appointments go in a flash (as we all know) and the disadvantaged populations in Baltimore just don‚Äôt have a shot to keep up. The disparity is REAL, and I don‚Äôt have the answer, but this seems to be a smart compassionate group. I‚Äôm just trying to brainstorm how to better serve and help my neighbors. Any thoughts, comments, helpful insights is much appreciated! All ideas welcome!

column1: ‚òØÔ∏è Connect The Dots  #ConnectDaDots ‚òØÔ∏è
column30: Somebody should stop the stupid here, but then again this is Florida! By Katie Shepherd April 27, 2021 at 4:28 a.m. CDT Last week, leaders at the Centner Academy, a Miami private school, sent teachers an email with a stark warning: Skip the coronavirus vaccines or else you‚Äôre not welcome in the classroom. ‚ÄúWe cannot allow recently vaccinated people to be near our students until more information is known,‚Äù the school‚Äôs co-founder Leila Centner said in a letter first reported on by the New York Times. Centner cited debunked misinformation to justify the policy, suggesting that ‚Äúreports have surfaced recently of non-vaccinated people being negatively impacted by interacting with people who have been vaccinated,‚Äù despite medical consensus that the coronavirus vaccines effectively prevent serious infections and carry few risks. The school‚Äôs decision alarmed public health experts and demonstrated the pervasive reach of misinformation about the vaccines, which have now been given to at least 141 million people in the United States. A dozen state attorneys general last month demanded that Facebook and Twitter do more to enforce policies against vaccine misinformation. The Centner Academy is in Miami‚Äôs swanky Design District, known for art galleries, shopping and architecture. Tuition starts at $15,160 for part-time preschoolers and runs up to $29,850 for its middle school students. Coronavirus vaccine makers have started clinical trials to test their vaccines on infants and teenagers, a crucial step toward controlling the pandemic. (Luis Velarde/The Washington Post) In her letter to teachers last week and a second note sent to parents on Monday, the school‚Äôs co-founder alluded to misinformation about the vaccines‚Äô impact on fertility and menstruation in women and girls and inaccurately suggested that vaccinated individuals ‚Äúmay be transmitting something‚Äù to unvaccinated people. Experts agree that vaccinated people cannot ‚Äúshed‚Äù the vaccines and spread their effects to unvaccinated individuals. None of the coronavirus vaccines approved for use in the United States have been linked to infertility, miscarriages or any other adverse impact on women‚Äôs reproductive health. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention recommends pregnant women get a coronavirus vaccine, after observing ‚Äúno safety concerns‚Äù among 35,000 women vaccinated during their third trimester. All of their babies were also healthy following the vaccinations, according to the CDC. The source of the unsupported concern in the letter is unclear, but the school has numerous public links with the anti-vaccination community. David and Leila Centner identify themselves as ‚Äúhealth freedom advocates,‚Äù and their school has posted guidance to help parents file for exemptions to state-required vaccinations. In late January, they invited Robert F. Kennedy Jr., a prominent anti-vaccine advocate, to speak at the school. Two prominent anti-vaccine advocates also publicly endorsed the school‚Äôs decision on Monday and said they have relatives enrolled at the Centner Academy. Christiane Northrup, an obstetrics and gynecology physician who promotes alternative medicine, posted on Facebook praising the school late Monday night. She posted a photo with Kelly Brogan, who co-runs an alternative health website and has a history of posting coronavirus misinformation on Instagram. Both women were identified in a report last month by the Center for Countering Digital Hate and Anti-Vax Watch as one of 12 individuals, dubbed the ‚ÄúDisinformation Dozen,‚Äù responsible for spreading up to 65 percent of coronavirus misinformation online. That report led Democratic Sens. Amy Klobuchar (Minn.) and Ben Ray Luj√°n (N.M.) to urge Facebook and Twitter to stop those prolific posters from ‚Äúspreading content that can harm the health of Americans.‚Äù After the report, Northrup defended her social media posts, arguing in a Facebook video that she would not ‚Äúbelieve in unfounded conspiracies and become involved in something that would result in such defamation.‚Äù Her social media accounts remain active. On Monday, Northrup again acknowledged the report while throwing her support behind the Centner Academy‚Äôs push to prevent teachers from getting the coronavirus vaccine. ‚ÄúSpent some time with Kelly Brogan, MD, one of my soul sisters and a fellow warrior who also made the famous Disinformation Dozen list,‚Äù Northrup wrote on Monday. ‚ÄúWe both have children (grandchildren in my case) who go to the Centner Academy, a miraculous school in Miami. We are keeping the vibration of joy and grounding as high as we possibly can!‚Äù Northrup in recent weeks has posted on Instagram and Facebook claiming, without evidence, that the coronavirus vaccines may be interfering with women‚Äôs periods. In her posts, she also promoted anti-vaccine groups, including Millions Against Medical Mandates and Maine Stands Up, which have opposed mask mandates, social-distancing-related restrictions and the widespread use of (truncated)

[despl√°cese hacia abajo para el resto del espa√±ol ] 1) yes, you can get second dose from massvax! - That question on the prereg in the Health section about 'have you had c19 vaccine in the past?' If you say yes, it then asks which one and when. * - if there's a no-appointment line, yes you can get 2nd dose through that, as long as you have your proof of first (vaccine card) and they're giving the matching vaccine. column1: ‚òØÔ∏è Connect The Dots  #ConnectDaDots ‚òØÔ∏è
column30: Original Post from Robert Slager : Epic Rant ... Monday morning quarterbacking is a cottage industry in the world of politics. The media is in overdrive this morning, offering a slew of reasons why Democrats underperformed in governor races in Virginia and New Jersey yesterday. They are claiming Democrats no longer have their finger on the pulse of the country. They are claiming this is a referendum on the Joe Biden presidency. They are claiming this is a sign of things to come in the 2022 mid-term elections. Deep cleansing breathes, people. The reason Democrats lost the governor's race in Virginia and underperformed in New Jersey is a lot more complicated than some in the media would have you believe. There is a great deal of fatigue in this country right now. People are weary of the pandemic. They are weary of high gas prices, inflation, short-staffed service businesses, and supply-chain issues. They are looking for someone to blame, and that blame - fairly or not - almost always falls on the party in power. The Biden administration is certainly open to legitimate criticism in some areas. We still don't have a coherent immigration policy. If the Democrats had passed some kind of infrastructure spending bill instead of constantly sniping at each other that may have tilted the balance in Virginia. But there are things that are simply out of the president's control. Biden doesn't set the price of crude oil throughout the world. Inflation was inevitable after the economic turbulence of the past two years. Supply-chain issues are also directly related to the pandemic. But many voters aren't interested in understanding the reason things happen. They just want someone to blame. Make no mistake about it - Republicans are doing everything they can to stretch this pandemic out as long as possible. Their entire strategy is to blame Democrats for not cleaning up the mess they left behind quickly enough. That's what their ridiculous anti-mask and anti-vax campaign is really all about. That's how callous they've become. They would literally rather have people die from a preventable disease than allow Biden to take credit for getting us out of the pandemic. The Supreme Court has repeated ruled that mandates are legal during a pandemic. Republicans in power know this. They know and they just don't care. But Democrats need to do some serious soul-searching before next year's election. They can't whine about being unable to compromise with Republicans when they can't even compromise within their own party. There is a political reality that cannot be ignored - Democrats do not have a big enough majority in the Senate to enact the sweeping changes that many progressives desire. Sometimes you literally do have to walk before you can run. As easy as it is to despise Joe Manchin and Kyrsten Sinema for not getting on board with the Build Back Better plan, some progress is better than no progress at all. The Biden administration needs a win heading into the 2022 mid-terms. That serves the ultimate goal of both moderates and progressives. Pick up a few more Senate seats, end the filibuster, and Manchin and Sinema no longer matter. And by this time next year the pandemic may finally be winding down. The political landscape could look a whole lot differently than it does right now. It is not all gloom-and-doom for Democrats. The new mayors of New York, Boston and Pittsburgh are all people of color. Strides are being made. We can still get there. But we can only get there together. -Robert Slager

!!!VACCINATION CERTIFICATE!!! 

*To all FULLY VACCINATED INDIVIDUALS, you may now access your national digital COVID-19 Vaccination Certificate!

The VaxCert is ONLY available at this site 48 hours after your 2nd dose vaccination: vaxcert.doh.gov.ph

Please browse photos for the steps in getting your vaccination certificate from the system. 

For those who has NO access to a computer, smart phone or internet connectivity, you may go to the VAXCERT ASSISTANCE BOOTH in the Municipal Gymnasium, Mondays- Fridays, except holidays (8 AM to 5 PM, except Fridays: 8 AM to 3 PM). 

***If there are problems in registration of VaxCert or if "" NO VACCINATION RECORD FOUND"" appears on the site after submitting the vaccination details, you can either:
a) Upload the photo of your vaccination card and any one (1) valid ID in the VaxCert System as instructed in the VaxCert site then wait for 48 hours to check again the availability of your Vax Cert in the system; or
b) E-mail the photo and details of your vaccination card and one (1) valid ID to this email: vaxcertph.ltb2601@gmail.com then wait for 48 hours to check again the availability of your VaxCert in the system; or
c) Go to the Assistance Booth in the Municipal Gymnasium which is open from Mondays to Fridays, except holidays (8 AM to 5 PM except Fridays: 8 AM to 3 PM)

***We apologize to some of our vaccinees since as of now, we are still on the process of encoding and editing vaccination details especially those who had their vaccination on the first months of our Resbakuna. Rest assured we are doing our best to upload all as soon as we can.

column30: When the Post article ran, it mentioned Hyattsville is still at only a 25% vax rate. I'm hoping that's changed in the time since. But the barbershop project is part of the national equity effort, and so since I've tracked down a donation link for the Center for Health Equity, I figure there are likely folks here who would also want to know about it.
column34: This is a re-share of a post
column35:
Back on 5/30 Washington Post had a story - * **""Barbershop offers coronavirus shots, in addition to cuts and shaves. Some see it as a national model.""*** The article mentions work to put together a graphic pamphlet for distribution around the country's barbershops, and that $50-75k needs to be raised. After a few emails, I was pointed to this donation link I'm sharing. 

UMD has been already working with barbershops for public health extension - teaching barbers to do blood pressure checks and discuss colon cancer screening.  In this case they've trained barbers to talk about reasons to vaccinate and address hesitancy, and they've set up clinics in barbershops.  The Biden administration is taking this project national.  Hopefully it, as well as the childcare and transportation help, as well as late night Fridays (which I only just learned about) will help us get to the people who are otherwise unserved. 

Here's the WaPo article; I'd been hoping the link would stay in the title above: https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2021/05/30/barbershop-coronavirus-vaccines/
---
Donations to the Maryland Center for Health Equity support the development of broad, multidisciplinary research initiatives to address racial and ethnic health disparities, including the Health Advocates In-Reach and Research (HAIR) campaign and the national ""Shots at the Shop"" initiative.
https://sph.umd.edu/research-impact/research-centers/maryland-center-health-equity

When I donated just now I put ""graphic novel fundraising"" in the ""in honor of,"" but there's also a place for comments after putting the credit card through, which is I think where that sort of note is supposed to go.

Spoke to gal with Feline Friends up in northern FL and she suggested I contact you regarding a foster/socialization situation for 3 Ginger boys. I have a unique urgent situation I'm seeking help with finding a foster for 3 beautiful 1 year old Ginger boys kitties I rescued July 2020 at the request of a friend who lived in a WPB condo community. the Condo Management were intent on eradicating this family and its young mama. i found trapper with a drop trap, who set about trapping them, as one was in trouble as the condo Management had set raccoon steel traps and caught the one ""Bobbie"" except, he wriggled back out only to lose most of his long tail to the trap. Bobbie, the bob-tail was super friendly due to surgeries, which allowed me to handle him, and consequently he was a mush and loved petting. I moved months later down the street in Singer Island to a larger condo on the water where I lived for 7 months at which time a buyer bought the property and I was forced to move. ‚ñ∫‚òÖ END UPDATE SUN JUN 6 8PM‚ñ∫‚òÖ 

PLEASE SAVE TITO! 
Tito came to me as a stray in March; Starving, infested and bleeding from mange, fleas and scrapes & scratches from lifelong neighborhood battles
Tito is an outdoor Street Survivor. He has the battle scars to prove it. But he‚Äôs friendly and a good loveable boy.

He loves to purr while he's being petted and groomed. He gives little love bites - the kind that don't draw blood or hurt.
PLEASE HELP! I'm moving and can't take him with me :(
Deb PrettyKitty Pachano helped me get him cleared up. Michele Cohen and others from Saving Sage had him lined up for no-cost neuter/vax/SNAP, but poor Tito came down with a runny nose, eye and sneezing & he lost his place in line for the free vet. 
I TNVRd him at Miami-Dade Animal Services Doral. 
He hasn‚Äôt left my front porch since!
He wants to be a lap dog ‚Äì he just needs somebody to give him the indoor time to decompress and he could very well be the perfect house kitty.
TitoTito loves affection, just within his boundaries. He‚Äôs not the type to cuddle, but  he likes being picked up and briefly made lap-kitty. He likes the comb. He loves gentle affection. He doesn‚Äôt like to be constrained or manhandled. 
He can be territorial; even after being fixed, he ran another cat off the property (he loves me!) Tito may do best as an only pet. Because of my limited space I have only been able to provide Tito with outdoor foster. I believe an indoor foster would totally mellow this good-hearted boy.
Tito has lived his whole life outdoors, but he likes it inside. He likes to come inside every time the door opens. He needs to be somebody‚Äôs indoor kitty.
Right now, he is fixed & vaccinated but he is still an outdoor cat, with a healthy dose of skittishness still. If you accidentally exceed his comfort zone and he spooks, he sometimes briefly snaps but immediately returns to his normal self. He‚Äôs a good boy.

He frequently comes when I call him; he stands up on his hind legs to greet me.      He follows me around the yard, and comes inside whenever invited .
He WANTS to be somebody‚Äôs furever indoor cat.
He NEEDS a savior! I‚Äôm moving and cannot take him with me.
PLEASE HELP FIND TITO A HOME!

column30: There has been such a big difference between how Germany and the US have handled the coronavirus pandemic. We must still wear masks (N95/FFP2 or surgical masks) in stores and on all public transportation. You can buy masks everywhere and they are very inexpensive. Indoor activities and hotels require one of the 3 Gs: Geimpft (vaccinated), Getestet (tested), or Genesung (recovery). There are simple apps for your phone that you can use for showing your status. They are free and the information can be loaded onto them free at any pharmacy. If you are tested, you get a QR code that you scan. Testing used to be free until the beginning of this month, but the cost is still low (about $20 for a single test with discounts for 5 or 10 tests). Yes, we have our anti-mask and anti-vax protesters here in Germany. But the vast majority of the people are rule followers or those who will scold you for not following the rules.

column30: Hey there, Much like you, I have been having a difficult time booking a vaccination appointment. As hard as it has been for me, it's been much more difficult for some of my older friends and family who are less tech savvy. It is for this reason that I created TurboVax. TurboVax is a browser extension which assists with scheduling a vaccination appointment at one of the MD MassVax sites. You can install the extension for your browser of choice (Chrome or Firefox) using one of the links below. Chrome: https://chrome.google.com/.../lhmlhlcpehgjmnhmkmgbdkdkjgf... Firefox: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/turbovax/ USAGE INSTRUCTIONS 1. Click the TurboVax icon in your browser's extension toolbar/menu. 2. In the resulting popup, read the instructions and select a vaccination site. 3. Proceed through the prompts for the vaccination site like normal. 4. TurboVax will pop in to help when searching for a vaccination site, and when searching for an appointment. 5. When a vaccination site, or an appointment is found the extension will play an audible alert to get your attention. I hope this extension simplifies the process for you and your family members. This eliminates the need to sit in front of the computer and manually refresh the vaccinations sites, and should make it easier for you to get vaccinated. CONTRIBUTING If you are proficient in HTML and JavaScript, consider contributing to the project on GitHub. It would be great to add additional vaccination sites. GitHub: https://github.com/jwosoft/TurboVax FEEDBACK If you have any feedback, feel free to hit me up on Facebook, or contact me via email at j.wo.soft@gmail.com.

column30: THE UNVACCINATED ARE MORE LIKE TO SPREAD THE VIRUS: According to the evidence, its absolute nonsense that the unvaccinated are more likely to spread the virus. In places like Gibraltar, Iceland and Israel where most or all of the populations are vaccinated, the infection rates remain high. Being vaccinated did not reduce the risk of transmission amongst fully, or largely vaccinated populations. Nearly 70% of Israel has been fully vaccinated and they already talking about a fourth vaccine. Secondly, observant folks would note we are at the stage in temperate climates when we would be anticipating high infection rates of influenza and hospital bed shortages, but nobody has been talking about rates of flu infection since Covid-19 appeared. Millions are infected with influenza or flu every year, with approx 300,000 to 600,000 dying worldwide every year. Keep an eye on the figures and compare this ongoing crisis with flu figures. Thirdly, we are waxing lyrical about increased infection rates of Omicron but just as with flu, we are not hearing of increased numbers of deaths Lastly, if governments are so certain these vaccines are safe, why did they sign away citizens rights to sue pharmaceutical companies for vaccine injury, or death? Governments can encourage vax uptake by agreeing to compensate for vaccine injury, or death. Why aren't pro-vaxers addressing that with the government? Is it easier to bully reluctant citizens?

column30: ALL are WELCOME at Rebel Gym Our GOAL is to make people HEALTHIER and STRONGER...not find ways to keep them from doing so. We all know staying FIT and ACTIVE reduces our chances of getting ""The Rona""...but let's not forget everything else out there like the Flu, Strep, a cold...not to mention Heart Disease, Diabetes and so much more! Rebel Gym didn't earn their ""Healthiest Work Environment"" award by forcing COVID Shots or Mask Mandates. We left it up to our staff and members because it is THEIR BODY and THEIR CHOICE. We showed them how to make healthy life choices & support them every step of the way. We have been operating on a mask & vax optional protocol for almost a year now and our clients and members have been thriving!! Being the cleanest gym in the county we take all precautions to be free of all types germs, that can cause all types of potential infections long before COVID was a thing. We continue to be vigilant in these tasks. We respect and keep each other safe by taking our personal health, fitness and hygiene seriously. Staying consistent with moving your body and with what you put in your body as far healthy food choices and needed vitamins is what we all need to be doing. At Rebel gym we help you with all of that...come join us! Be Strong Be Determined be a REBEL!! #rebelgymmahopac #maskoptional #vaxoptional #yourbody #yourchoice #BeStrong #BeDetermined #beaREBEL #justgetyourtrainingdone #disclpineequalsfreedom #projectstandtogether

column30: PTPA To ensure the safety of everyone and to abide with the updated IATF-EID Guidelines, we would like to inform our guests and patrons that Lapastora Resort will no longer allow unvaccinated individuals on the resort premises. Children aged 11 years old and below are still allowed but the guardians must be fully vaccinated. PUBLIC ADVISORY:
To ensure the safety of everyone and to abide with the updated IATF-EID Guidelines, we would like to inform our guests and patrons that Lapastora Resort will no longer allow unvaccinated individuals on the resort premises. Nanolipid components in the Pfzer-BioNTech vaccine include: ((4-hydroxybutyl)azanediyl)bis(hexane-6,1- diyl)bis(2-hexyldecanoate), 2 [(polyethylene glycol)-2000]- N,N-ditetradecylacetamide, 1,2-distearoyl-sn-glycero-3- phosphocholine, and cholesterol - Salts: Helping to balance the acidity in your body, the following salts are included in the Pfzer-BioNTech vaccine: potassium chloride, monobasic potassium phosphate, sodium chloride, and dibasic sodium phosphate dihydrate - Sugar: Basic table sugar, also known as sucrose, can also be found in the Pfzer-BioNTech vaccine. This ingredient helps the molecules maintain their shape during freezing. ‚Ä¢ Does NOT contain: Eggs, Preservatives, Latex Learn more, read the FDA full Pfzer-BioNTech Fact Sheet: www.fda.gov/media/144414/download Moderna Vaccine ‚Ä¢ 94% efective ‚Ä¢ Number of shots: 2 shots, 28 days apart ‚Ä¢ Approved for use in people aged 18 years and older ‚Ä¢ Ingredients: messenger ribonucleic acid (mRNA), lipids (SM-102, polyethylene glycol [PEG] 2000 dimyristoyl glycerol [DMG], cholesterol, and 1,2-distearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine [DSPC]), tromethamine, tromethamine hydrochloride, acetic acid, sodium acetate, and sucrose ‚Ä¢ Explanation of ingredients: - mRNA: Like the Pfzer BioNTech vaccine, Moderna‚Äôs also uses mRNA technology to build antibodies against COVID-19. - Lipids: Nanolipids help deliver the mRNA to the vaccine recipient‚Äôs cells. Nanolipid components of the Moderna vaccine include: (SM-102, 1,2-dimyristoyl-rac-glycero3- methoxypolyethylene glycol-2000 [PEG2000-DMG], cholesterol, and 1,2-distearoyl-snglycero-3-phosphocholine [DSPC]) - The remaining ingredients, including acids (acetic acid), acid stabilizers (tromethamine and tromethamine hydrochloride), salt (sodium acetate), and sugar (sucrose) all work together to maintain the stability of the vaccine after it‚Äôs produced. ‚Ä¢ Does NOT contain: Eggs, Preservatives, Latex Learn more, read the FDA full Moderna Fact Sheet: www.fda.gov/media/144638/download Getting vaccinated is one of many steps you can take to protect yourself and others from COVID-19. For some people, COVID-19 can cause severe illness or death. Getting vaccinated not only protects you from COVID-19, it also protects those around you by preventing its spread. Stopping a pandemic requires using all the prevention tools available. Vaccines work with your immune system so your body will be ready to fght the virus. Other steps, like masks and social distancing, help reduce your chance of being exposed to the virus and spreading it to others. Together, COVID-19 vaccination and following CDC‚Äôs recommendations to protect yourself and others will ofer the best protection from COVID-19. column30: **An urgent message from Jim Walsh:** Most of you filled out jotform already. Included here is more info: **Urgent actions to take against the Statewide Mandatory Covid Vax for children. ** You can do Step 1 only, or do both steps. Email, calling/leaving a voicemail. **Step 1: ** Please review, sign if you agree and share, we need to gather as many signatures as possible and turn into WABOH as public comment. https://form.jotform.com/220043702752041 Just tap on the above address to enter your name, city name, and your signature. Then send it to as many as you can. WA Board of Health meets Wednesday to discuss. (Even if its to late for that meeting, they will still get it). **Step 2: ** Washington State Board of Health https://sboh.wa.gov/ **Please email the Board members @ wsboh@sboh.wa.gov** **Call them @ 360-236-4110** Sample email message: *Hello, Washington State Board of Health, (Put in your own words) I am writing to you to request you not put the Covid-19 Vaccination as a requirement for children to go to school in Washington State. What you are requiring is against the constitution and against science. This is against the people's will. The Covid-19 vaccine is experimental and there are reports of injuries and deaths. See FB page for names of board members to write to or call.* BE POLITE BUT FIRM IN YOUR CONVICTION please. Thanks

column1: Mississippi Work From Home Moms and Dads
column30: Hey guys. As a mom I have started a new business. I am looking for someone who is willing to help me cover outbound cold calls Monday-Friday. I am flexible. You can pick the hours you work daily. I get being a parent! I have a toddler and am expecting in April. (That‚Äôs why I need help with calls-my house is far from quiet!) Requirements: -comfortable on the phone or willing to learn. -you will need a smartphone to be able to access our phone dialing app. -ability to adapt to each phone call. This will not be traditional sales. I will train you personally with how I like calls handled. -WiFi or cell service with data. -CashApp or PayPal to receive payments weekly. -a quiet work space. -available anytime between 8am-6pm EST to make calls based on time zones. -an email address to receive work. -willing to work alone at your own pace and keep in communication regularly with me. -a positive attitude. -must be in the USA and speak fluent English. Not required: -No COVID vax required. You are working remotely and your health is your personal choice. I have no right to enforce something like this on you. -computer or laptop. This will make life easier on you, but you can do everything from you phone. -experience. It‚Äôs a plus, but not required. I am looking for something altogether different when it comes to call handling. These will not be rushed calls, but rather really getting to know the customer and their needs so that we can help them grow as well. The position will be long term with bonuses per contract that you close. It will be contract hourly without additional benefits. There will be a 2 week trial period for all new team members. Starting pay is $4/hour (including training) plus bonuses monthly at 1% or the total monthly account value for the first full 3 months of the account longevity. Raises are a big possibility as we grow. Minimum 10 hours per week, but you can work as much as you would like if there are contacts to reach out to. Please comment if you are interested and I‚Äôll message you.

column30: HALF PRICE IN-HOME VACUUM SERVICE!! Dyson | Shark | Kirby | Miele | Sebo | Oreck | Vax | Gtech Q: WHAT HAPPENS DURING A SERVICE?.. A: The service takes place in the convenience of your home at a time that suits you. It generally takes about 45 minutes during which your Dyson will be stripped down to the motor cleaning all internal parts, carry out a comprehensive 52 point check, break and down the cyclone assembly clearing all blockages. As it is rebuilt all parts are checked and analysed to ensure they are in good order i.e seals, cables, filters, hoses. If new parts are required then they can be supplied at an additional cost.
